e, where zinesters persistently and stubbornly carve out new spaces for what it means to be a revolutionary and a girl. Girl Zines takes zines seriously, asking what they can tell us about the inner lives of girls and women over the last twenty years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 4aGirl. 4aabout. 4aasking. 4agirls. 4ainner. 4alast. 4alives. 4aover. 4aseriously. 4atakes. 4atell. 4athey. 4atwenty. 4awhat. 4awomen. 4ayears. 4azines. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh1 aZeisler, Andi08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814768501423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814768501.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK